    Builds a ViewElementFieldset for a property.

    The property can have a EntityAttributes.FIELDSET_PROPERTY_SELECTOR attribute specifying the selector that should be used to fetch the members of the fieldset. If none is available a default will be created for all child properties.

    In addition the EntityPropertyDescriptor may contain a custom template function as the ViewElementFieldset.TEMPLATE attribute value. If this is the case, that template will be used for rendering the fieldset.

    When requesting a fieldset in ViewElementMode.FORM_WRITE, tooltip, description and help text for the property will be added to ViewElementFieldset.getTitle(), ViewElementFieldset.getHeader() and ViewElementFieldset.getFooter() respectively.
